title: Trump threatens 'automatic 10 years in prison' for anyone harming statues: 'If they even try'
description: President Trump issued a warning Sunday morning to anyone who even attempts to harm federal monuments, including the Lincoln or Jefferson Memorials, saying that they will automatically face a substantial prison term.

title: DeVos vows to have schools open in fall: 'Kids have got to get back to school'
description: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos said Sunday that she intends to have American schools open for in-person classes this fall, and insisted that this can be done safely despite concerns over the coronavirus pandemic.

title: Val Demings' police background could complicate her Biden VP chances
description: U.S. Rep. Val Demings’ background as Orlando, Fla.'s first female police chief could complicate her chances of becoming Joe Biden’s running mate.

title: Louisville mayor upstaged by protesters at news conference: video
description: It appears nobody had Louisville Mayor Greg Fischer’s back during a news conference on Friday.

title: Trump administration announces 25 percent tariff on $1.3B in French handbags, cosmetics, other goods
description: The White House announced a 25 percent tariff on $1.3 billion worth of French merchandise on Saturday, including cosmetics and handbags, after a digital service tax was levied against U.S. tech giants.

title: UN Security Council passes resolution authorizing cross-border aid to Syria, after Russian opposition
description: The U.N. Security Council on Saturday passed a resolution authorizing a Syrian aid program that will deliver aid to the rebel-held northwest via just one border crossing -- after previous efforts to authorize more crossings were torpedoed by Russia and China.

title: Robert Mueller defends Stone conviction, Russia investigation after sharp criticism from White House
description: Former Special Counsel Robert Mueller on Saturday vigorously defended his team's decision to prosecute Roger Stone, stopping short of directly attacking President Trump, who commuted Stone's sentence the day prior.
